<table bgcolor="#000000" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor="#000000"  width="100%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#404070" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post164008"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>BrikBludgaard</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Reaver</font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Registered: Apr 2002<br>
<!--	Location: <br>
	Posts: 253-->
</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#404070" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ><img src="images/icons/icon1.gif" border="0" alt=""> <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Greater Disciplines would be designed for long-term use...<br />
meaning their bonuses and penalties would even out and not be the huge bonuses meant for the older-style disciplines.<br />
<br />
Warrior would be ABLE to deal melee damage as if they were a ranger, but have to give up much of their defensive abilities to do so. (note they could not use the old /disc defensive while in an aggressive stance until 1 minute had passed)<br />
<br />
The idea here would be to allow the striaght melee classes some more versatility...  at the cost of a little inconvenience somewhere else.<br />
<br />
Warriors would ALWAYS be better at absorbing damage period.<br />
<br />
Knights would be second place guaranteed.<br />
<br />
ALL classes would have some long range punch, but only the ranger would be able to make it into something anywhere near melee damage....  rangers would have to be in the point-blank bubble to get the ultimate in bow damage. (and thus risk) this fixes much of the PvP issues as well.<br />
<br />
<br />
The goal is overall melee changes to make it more fair and more varied for everyone...<br />
<br />
Dual wield, 2H, and 1H+shield should all be viable and have their advantages and disadvantages.<br />
<br />
I am trying to set 1H and 2H on even terms except for their native advanatges/disadvantages....  Rangers have 240 defense, so 235 weaponskills and offense seem to make sense....  <br />
Given the degree of changes for dual wielders, I feel this was necessary for knights to stay in the ballpark...  240? 235? sure...  245 is pushing in my opinion.<br />
<br />
Yep, Paladins, Rangers, Rogues, monks, beastlord all need 61+ disciplines designed for them.  Paladin's discplines probably need to be totally redesigned.<br />
<br />
Brik</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
