	<td bgcolor="#303070" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ><img src="images/icons/icon1.gif" border="0" alt=""> <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Brik, i agree with all that u have addressed as far as discs not stacking etc.<br />
<br />
However i honestly dont see a need for warriors or knights to become any better at taking damage, i think we are perfectly fine as is for now.  The reason i dont see a need for tanks to take damage better, is we already have several guild in time, and lots of guilds are in the elemental planes, all of this has ben done with the current tanks, so an upgrade in that department is not needed.<br />
<br />
I do like the idea of warriors to be able to be more versitile through giving up X to gain Y.  IMO warriors are a pretty simple class, and versitility would add to the class, as wel as m ake them much more desireble in exp groups, something they really need.<br />
<br />
As far as solo, I actually like that melees cant solo, i think this is as it should be.  Leme explain why, in a exp group the most important thing is consistant damage, in order to keep up with spawns and a good pull rate which yelieds a good stable rate of exp.  Melee have pretty much constand DPS, Casters on the other hand are burst dps, casters rely on mana.   <br />
<br />
This means 1 thing, in order for casters vs melee to be balanced, casters need to have higher burst damage, and melee will have higher long term damage.<br />
<br />
If the above statement is true, there is almost no reason to have a wizard in a group over a rogue, because with a rogue u gain constant dps, with a wizard, he oly nukes when he has mana.  Due to this melee are gona be much more group friendly, while casters will tend to solo.  This is why casters MUST have a solo advantage, because melees inately have a group advantage.<br />
<br />
SK being both caster and melee, fall in between, we can kinda solo, but are basicly a grouping class.</font></p>
	
